<div class="col1a evencols">
<div class="col1b evencols">

<h2>Intern and Educator Opportunities</h2>

<div class="spot80">
<img src="/edu/gfx/intern_200.jpg" style="width:80px;height:80px" alt="*" />
<p><b>Internships</b><br />
All about high school and undergraduate student internships at NASA/GISS and its NYC-area research partners.<br />
<a href="intern/">+ Read More</a></p>
</div><!-- spot80 -->

<div class="spot80">
<img src="/edu/gfx/ccri80.jpg" style="width:80px;height:80px" alt="*" />
<p><b>Climate Change Research Initiative</b><br />
Year-round STEM engagement program allowing educators and graduate students to work directly with NASA scientists, with a summer internship program.<br />
<a href="ccri/">+ Read More</a></p>
</div><!-- spot80 -->

</div><!-- col1b -->
</div><!-- col1a -->











<div class="col2a evencols">
<div class="col2b evencols">

<h2>Advanced Study Programs</h2>

<div class="spot80" style="margin-bottom:12px">
<img src="/edu/gfx/cu_200.png" style="width:80px;height:80px" alt="*" />
<p><b>Columbia University Graduate Study</b><br />
Study toward an advanced degree in the atmospheric sciences may be conducted at GISS through enrollment at Columbia University.<br />
<a href="/edu/grad/">+ Read More</a></p>
</div><!-- spot80 -->


<div class="spot80">
<img src="/edu/gfx/postdoc_200.jpg" style="width:80px;height:80px" alt="*" />
<p><b>Postdoctoral Research Programs</b><br />
Advanced programs in which early career scientists may participate in GISS research include NASA and Columbia University postdoctoral appointments.<br />
<a href="/about/jobs/postdoc.html">+ Read More</a></p>
</div><!-- spot80 -->

</div><!-- col2b -->
</div><!-- col2a -->





<div class="col1a evencols">
<div class="col1b evencols">

<h2>Past Programs</h2>

<div class="spot80" style="margin-bottom:12px">
<img src="/edu/gfx/nycri80.jpg" style="width:80px;height:80px" alt="*" />
<p><b>New York City Research Initiative</b><br />
Intern and educator program in which teams of students worked with GISS scientists and affiliated university researchers. NYCRI concluded in 2014.<br />
<a href="nycri/">+ Read More</a></p>
</div><!-- spot80 -->

<div class="spot80">
<img src="/edu/gfx/icp80.gif" style="width:80px;height:80px" alt="*" />
<p><b>GISS Institute on Climate and Planets</b><br />
A collaborative program between GISS, Columbia University, and the City University of New York. ICP concluded in 2004<br />
<a href="https://icp.giss.nasa.gov/">+ Go to Website</a></p>
</div><!-- spot80 -->

</div><!-- col1b -->
</div><!-- col1a -->










<div class="col2a evencols">
<div class="col2b evencols">

<h2>Resource Materials</h2>

<p><b>CCRI STEM Curriculum Modules</b><br />
Instructional modules developed during the GISS Climate Change Research Initiative and NASA/SMD approved.<br />
<a href="res/">+ Read More</a>
</p>

<!--
<p><b>Education GCM</b><br />
The EdGCM project at the Columbia University Center for Climate Systems Research couples GISS Model II with a user-friendly interface that runs on macOS and Windows desktop computers.
<br />
<a href="http://edgcm.columbia.edu/">+ Go to Website</a></p>
-->

<p><b>ICP Educational Materials Archive</b><br />
Curriculum modules and learning tools developed during the Institute for Climate and Planets program (1994-2004) for use in classroom learning about climate and environmental research.<br />
<a href="https://icp.giss.nasa.gov/education/">+ Read More</a>
</p>

</div><!-- col2b -->
</div><!-- col2a -->









